%% Data Flow Diagram - Models as a Service (MaaS)
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as maas-default-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Authorino as Kuadrant/Authorino
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Limitador as Kuadrant/Limitador
    participant Backend as LLMInferenceService<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Client,Backend: Flow 1: Model Inference with API Key Authentication
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>Auth: Bearer sk-oai-*<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
        Gateway->>Authorino: Auth check (internal)
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+ (SIMPLE)
        MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: Validate API key hash<br/>5432/TCP
        PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Key metadata + user identity
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: ValidationResult<br/>(username, groups, key-id)
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /v1/subscriptions/select<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Selected subscription tier
        Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth OK + identity headers<br/>X-MaaS-Username, X-MaaS-Group, X-MaaS-Key-Id
        Gateway->>Limitador: Token rate limit check<br/>(auth.identity from Authorino)
        Limitador-->>Gateway: Rate limit OK
        Gateway->>Backend: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8080 (internal)
        Backend-->>Gateway: Inference response
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>HTTPS/443
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over Client,PostgreSQL: Flow 2: API Key Management
        Client->>Gateway: POST /maas-api/v1/api-keys<br/>Auth: Bearer (API key or K8s token)<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
        Gateway->>Authorino: Auth check (dual: API key + K8s tokenReview)
        Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth OK + X-MaaS-Username
        Gateway->>MaaSAPI: Forward to /v1/api-keys<br/>HTTP/8080 or HTTPS/8443
        MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: Create/query API key<br/>5432/TCP
        PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Result
        MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: API key response (sk-oai-* shown once on create)
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Client,Backend: Flow 3: MaaSAuthPolicy Reconciliation
        Note over MaaSAPI: maas-controller watches CRDs
        MaaSAPI->>Gateway: Watch MaaSAuthPolicy CRs<br/>K8s API 443/TCP TLS 1.2+
        MaaSAPI->>Gateway: Get MaaSModelRef, HTTPRoute<br/>K8s API 443/TCP
        MaaSAPI->>Gateway: Create/Update Kuadrant AuthPolicy<br/>K8s API 443/TCP
        Note over Gateway: AuthPolicy targets model HTTPRoute<br/>with API key validation callback URL
    end
